show_title: Warplet Mania: When Purple Monsters Broke Farcaster: GM Farcaster ep304 with @shawmakesmagic
text:
We‚Äôre building an ecosystem that is agent powered to take on the kinds of agentic tasks that web2 isn‚Äôt exploring.

Agents that negotiate. Agents that predict. Agents that play. Agents that bet. Agents that attack, and agents that protect.

This is powered by some new tech like x402, wallet abstraction, paymasters and identity registry, and running on a layer 3 app chain that lets any token on Base join up like a native gas token, provided they bring some liquidity to the chain and pick it.

Swap, pools, perps, prediction markets, on chain games, tokens and marketplace, all with frontends for agents and humans to play together.

We providing free indexing of all on chain data, free RPC endpoints and direct access to all on chain services through a web2 API wrapper with x402 payment rails.

This is called Jeju. It‚Äôs integrated with elizaOS cloud, which bridges our web2 user base to all services running on chain.

We‚Äôll show more in December.

text:
Warplet lore:

On Sunday night I was weighing more complex traits or just shipping it.

I had this queued up for the night:
Use past casts to add an ‚Äúaffinity‚Äù to each Warplet.

Affinities would be Farcaster icons like degen hat, bracky sports items, etc

I chose to just ship it ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è

But one cool bit: each Warplet does have unique traits. That‚Äôs how the images get created. I saved the traits as json but chose to put them on chain because they‚Äôre all pretty much unique and not OpenSea friendly. Maybe I‚Äôll dump them somewhere.

cast.text: AI generative collections in the style of Warplets remain severely underexplored. You can use user identity + input not just for an image but for traits, etc. Cocreation plus randomization seems very interesting. Rarity becomes based in part on luck but also past behavior, identity, and even skill and creativity.
